Package bio.singa.structure.model.interfaces

Interface LeafSubstructure<FamilyType extends StructuralFamily>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AtomContainer, Exchangeable<FamilyType>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AminoAcid, Ligand, Nucleotide
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MmtfAminoAcid, MmtfLeafSubstructure, MmtfLigand, MmtfNucleotide, OakAminoAcid, OakLeafSubstructure, OakLigand, OakNucleotide
    public interface LeafSubstructure<FamilyType extends StructuralFamily>
extends AtomContainer, Exchangeable<FamilyType>
    A leaf substructure is a collection of atoms with meta data assigned to it. A leaf substructure can be part of a macro molecule, such as amino acid residues or nucleotides, or independent small molecules.

      • getIdentifier

        LeafIdentifier getIdentifier()
        Returns the complete leaf identifier. The leaf identifier consists of the PDB identifer, the model identifier, the chain identifier, the serial of the leaf substructure and optionally an insertion code.

      • flatToString

        default java.lang.String flatToString()
        Returns the flat String representation of this leaf substructure in the form: 
             [LeafIdentifier] [ThreeLetterCode]
        For example: 
             1C0A-1-B-631 C
     1C0A-1-A-78 ARG
     1C0A-1-A-1048 HOH
        Returns:
        The flat String representation of this leaf substructure.
